<br>
Sunstorm, &quot;uber&quot; conj mage:<br>
2400 damage for 440 mana nominal.<br>
<br>
Bonus to damage: 14%<br>
Reduction to mana use (by your assumptions): 32.5%<br>
Reduct to mana use (my figures): 20.25%<br>
mitigation: 25%<br>
<br>
Ex post damage: 2052<br>
Ex post mana: 297<br>
Ex post mana (my figures):  350<br>
ex post DPM: 6.9<br>
ex post DPM (my figures):5.86<br>
<br>
Sun vortex:<br>
1550 for 395 nominal<br>
Donus to damage: 24.5%<br>
Reduction to mana use: 40%<br>
red to mana use (my figures): 28%<br>
Ex post damage: 1937.5<br>
ex post mana: 237<br>
ex post mana<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  my figures): 285<br>
DPM (yours): 8.2<br>
DPM(mine): 6.8<br>
<br>
But what about short run DPS? You presume you just chain sunstorm, but a rain chainer will typically string sunstorm, maelstrom, and possibly shock of sun.<br>
<br>
Case one: sunstorm + maelstrom chain.<br>
Cast sunstorm (3.4 seconds), wait 2.2 seconds (could skip with telescope), cast maelstrom (5.1 seconds) total of 10.7 seconds, then telescope and wait 1.3 seconds for sunstorm to refresh and repeat. Therefore one sunstorm and one maelstrom per 12 seconds.<br>
Maelstrom damage is:<br>
2700 plus 14%, mitigated for 25% = 2308.5<br>
Totall damage for two spells: 4360.5<br>
DPS over 12 seconds: 363<br>
<br>
This short run DPS blows sun vortex stringing out of the water by over 50%. I can also report that this combination is at most as aggro inducing as chaining sun vortex; if anything it induces less aggro. So rains are better if you have plenty of mana and want tremendous short run DPS.<br>
<br>
Consider another strategy: sun storm then right click sceptre of burning elements. Sun storm takes 3.4 seconds, sceptre 8 seconds, therefore wait 0.6 seconds to repeat the cycle. This does, by my figures, 6.57 DPM with a DPS of 191.8<br>
<br>
Compare to chaining sun vortex. Each sun vortex is about 5.35 seconds, plus 2.2 second recasts, so a total of 7.55. As shown above, DPM is 6.8; DPS is 255.6; so sunstorm + sceptre is a bad strategy.<br>
<br>
Third case, for magic resistant mobs: sun storm followed by firebolt, again with telescopes can do every 12 seconds. Bolt damage is: 2241 with a 10% mitigation;so this would again be an inferior strategy if the mob is vulnerable to magic. 2490 without the 10% mitigation, so if you wanted to max out short run DPS when you were certain bolts would land, this would be the way to go.<br>
<br>
Would maelstrom +bolt work? maelstrom is 5.1 seconds; bolt is 5.95 seconds. So it would work using telescopes/jboots/other instaclicks. Without bolt mitigation this would be 2490+2308=4798 or 400 DPS. That's basically the maximum short run possible DPS. <p>Master Cydmab Promethean<br>
Arch Convoker of Morell Thule<br>
Fury's Edge</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A> at: 1/21/03 7:52:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nemuneir>Nemuneir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 9:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1752.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DD Comparison -- Graphical Format</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the analysis Cydmab.<br>
<br>
Why do you say my assumptions are wrong?  I'm not shooting in the dark, I've done a bit of research on them.  Mage researchers disagree with Graffe's common belief that SCM3 is 10%.  I'm less certain about the ear being 15% fixed mana reduction, but I do remember seeing some research on it.<br>
<br>
The reason there's no analysis in my charts for chain-nuking is because... well, that's not what I was analyzing.  Originally, I wanted to know which nuke to use while exping.  The logical choice is the best dpm ratio, which is why I found these charts useful.  Another interesting aspect is DPS, I decided to include that too.<br>
<br>
I didn't presume you'd just chaincast vortex, I only wanted to show what using your time casting vortex is good for. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Nemuneir Noldaron<br>
Arch-Mage of Vallis Aspectus<br>
Ayonae Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2729<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 10:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1752.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DD Comparison -- Graphical Format</span><hr size=1> When I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">tested</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the summoned focus earring, I got about 10% mana savings with no signs of randomness.  However, after all my reading, I am willing to accept random between 1% and 15% or on average 8% mana savings.  That would be within the tolerances of my experiments.<br>
<br>
It is much harder to do repeatable experiments on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as the only opportunity you have to test it is just before and after you get the ability.  You cannot turn it off in order to compare.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>ShowEQ</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> advocates purport to have determined that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> amounts to 11% mana savings, but I am not pursuaded.  First, they make their conclusion based on the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">structure</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> of the data packet, and assume that their <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">interpretation</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> is obvious and factual.  Once cannot derive the semantics or meaning of data from its syntax or structure.  Second, I think the number they bandy about is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">displayed</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> mana, not <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">actual</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> mana, and we know for a fact that these are often out of sync and different from one another.<br>
<br>
However, when we are talking 8% or 10%, it matters not much.  As long as we can tell good idea from bad idea, then that is sufficient.<br>
<br>
At the bottom line, I am an empericist.  I will test whatever hypothesis as necessary.<br>
<br>
