<br>
In response to your points:<br>
<br>
The purpose of these charts isn't as an absolute reference for dpm/dps -- it is meant to be a comparison of the value of different DD's in different AA / Specialization / focus item scenarios.  That being said:<br>
<br>
1) My mitigation value of 25% for rains was intended to indicate that rains are 25% less effective at delivering damage than their more direct cousins.  I'm not trying to imply that DD spells have 0% resist.  Keep in mind I'm also considering damage lost to waves landing at under 10% mob health and the movement of the target out of the AoE before all rains can land.  The 25% number is not well substantiated, but I believe it to be in the ballpark.  A 'correct' number is not calculatable, since different situations and/or players will obviously see this mitigation value vary drastically.<br>
<br>
2) My assumption that 1 in 10 bolts is blocked is based on my personal experience hunting in group situations.  In any case where I find myself in close quarters, I find many bolts being blocked because of unpredicted movements, the long casting time of FoT, and the 'archery bug' related to mobs pushed against walls.  I agree that different people, and different situations, will see varying mitigation numbers -- but I stand by 10% as a reasonable estimate of all of those scenarios.<br>
<br>
I would challenge you to pay closer attention to your bolt misses -- I find that even when I'm being as careful as possible, its extremely difficult to ensure that every bolt will hit.  Keep in mind the point of these charts is to help the more casual mage decide which DD to load and use as their <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>primary weapon</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in experience-grinding combat -- switching to a different nuke for anything but extremely specialized situations defeats this purpose.  How often can you make bolts work when they're your only form of direct damage?<br>
