<br>
I will come back to you again on this, if I may, as I feel you are ignoring factual measured data and reports from experienced bolt users, and so allowing 'bad advice' to be perpetuated.<br>
<br>
1) I know you said, and indeed intended to say, you believe rains to be 25% less effective at delivering damage than DDs/Bolts due to resist rates. I am not sure you understood however, that the data from my own study pretty much PROVES that this cannot be true, as over a large number of data points, the loss of damage from 'perfect' is only 24.6%, and DDs/Bolts themselves cannot possibly be considered perfect (considering resists). This is why, I maintain that in the absence of a detailed study looking at the resist rate of DDs/Bolts, a relative damage mitigation figure of between 15% and 20% for rains compared to DDs/Bolts would be more accurate and objective, based on real evidence.<br>
<br>
It is a figure, it is not vital, but for advice to the casual mage, as you put it, you should be using the data presented to you or refuting it with detailed data of your own, not just claiming your 'gut feel' to be of more relevance.<br>
<br>
It should be noted, that you had an implicit assumption that the resist rate for DDs and Bolts are the same. However, this is not at all an unreasonable assumption, I feel, so any measurement of one could be used as a measure of the other, in the absence of both.<br>
<br>
2) Your position on bolts, sir, is manifestly untenable.<br>
<br>
Here is the maths, using your gear setup, for FoT for the Evoc mage at 65:<br>
<br>
Mana: 500 -40% (SCM3, Earring, Spec200 Evoc) = 300<br>
Dmg: 2000 +24% (FoM3, Bracer) = 2480<br>
Casting Time: 7.0 + 2.25 = 9.25 - 10% (Ring) = 8.325seconds<br>
Therefore:<br>
<br>
FoT: DPM = 8.27, DPS = 297.90<br>
<br>
Compare to SunVortex for the Conjure Mage:<br>
<br>
SV: DPM = 8.11 DPS = 248.32<br>
<br>
You challenged me 'to you to pay closer attention to your bolt misses -- I find that even when I'm being as careful as possible, its extremely difficult to ensure that every bolt will hit'.<br>
<br>
Well, last night, I did precisely this, in a typical Bastion of Thunder xp grind group, 6 players, sandstorm giants. In just over 2 hours, I used exclusively FoT for damage. I cast it over 100 times. I missed: zero.<br>
<br>
This, sir, is not special for me. Yes I was trying especially hard NOT to lose any bolts, but unless I am relaxing or messing about, I usually concentrate on positioning, angles and such all the time anyway, and shout at groups that are not bolt and water pet friendly until they learn (*grin*), so I rarely lose many anyway.<br>
<br>
Now, I am only level 63 with FoM II at this moment, but assuming I do not lose my bolt-using skills, I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>will</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be achieving DPM 8.27 DPS 297.90 (reduced by resists) with FoT, or very close to it, under a wide range of my typical hunting scenarios, when I hit 65/FoM III. And when I do, the conjuration mage's DPM 8.11 DPS 248.32 (equally reduced by resists) with FV is going to look weaker (that DPS difference really bites hard).<br>
<br>
The fact that there are circumstances when evocationalist magi such as myself *do* load and use DDs, even Conjuration DDs, and indeed perhaps even drop FoT, is not at all relevant in the analysis of the DPM / DPS achievable with FoT under the wide range of circumstances when it can be used as the main damage spell.<br>
<br>
If you are going to refute any of this, you will need hard evidence. At the moment, your refute simply seems to be 'I can't use bolts that well, and neither can my conjuration magi friends, so no-one can'. I am very sorry sir, but in this, you are badly mistaken.<br>
