</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nemuneir>Nemuneir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(2/12/03 9:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1752.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: destroy summoned</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I haven't had much time lately to respond to this.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So to answer your question, I would use 17.5% (though I accept 20% as not unreasonable) and 2.0% (which is what I think I could achieve on average in the places I XP, using the tactics I employ).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm still not convinced a change from 25% resist on rains is called for.  The data from wizards indicating lure-based rains still have 25% resist is very persuasive.<br>
<br>
As for bolts, I will drop my mitigation on the bolts from 10% to 7.5% (1:10 to ~1:15) as soon as I get the chance.  2% still seems low, given my personal experience.  I still believe 1 miss in 50 is pretty spectacular for 'casual' nuking.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>whilst your figures might have relevance to the 'average' mage (whatever that is exactly), why aim at the 'average' mage at all? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I suppose my overall goal for this chart was originally to help my guild mages to improve their effectiveness.  I would like mages to know which nuke to use to be most effective.  The mage who is as obsessive as myself (or Suzanna) doesn't need the help of silly charts to maximize our effectiveness -- we're anal enough to crunch the numbers ourselves.<br>
<br>
I suppose I'm making the (possibly invalid) assumption that mages who are un-obsessive enough to rely on a chart for their DD selection will also be rather non-driven to prevent bolt blockage.<br>
<br>
It's those people I'm hoping this chart will help, so I'd like it to represent their playing experience as well as possible.<br>
<br>
- Nemuneir Noldaron<br>
Arch-Convoker of Vallis Aspectus<br>
